problem_data.title: Permutations
problem_data.description: Given an array nums of distinct integers, return all the possible permutations. You can return the answer in any order.
problem_data.solution:
class Solution(object):
    def permute(self, nums):
        """
        :type nums: List[int]
        :rtype: List[List[int]]
        """
        res = []

        def backtrack(start):
            if start == len(nums):
                res.append(nums[:])
                return
            for i in range(start, len(nums)):
                nums[start], nums[i] = nums[i], nums[start]
                backtrack(start + 1)
                nums[start], nums[i] = nums[i], nums[start]

        backtrack(0)
        return res
